column11: Bucks County Council for The Aging
column55: Daughter, Robin L. Polonsky, age 62 permanently/totally disabled. Spouse, Barbara H. Polonsky, age 89, currently debilitated as a result of stroke. Presently in rehab/nursing facility.

I am so grateful food and toiletries box I receive every month. Your organization is amazing. You help people no matter who they are based on needs and compassionate respect for all. Your organization may be a "Jewish" organization, but to me your organization is for anyone who needs a little extra help. Thank you so much. The food items are so good. I love the canned vegetables, and I like all of my food items. I especially love the potato pancake mix and packages to make soup. I was born and raised in the "South" - Georgia. My family always had fresh fruit, vegetables, and smoked meats. My mom and dad always had a garden and caught fresh fish. My parents are no longer here, but your services remind remind me of my parents. They would help anyone, provide food to eat, a place to stay, a hug, and most of all a dedication to "Giving".
I appreciate all that the JRA has done for me and my family.
The produce usually comes very bruised, inedible, and my kids will not eat it. Too many onions and garlic.

I love the grape juice, thank you for the food box! I will move on February 28, 2022. Rent will be $775.00 at the new apartment in the northeast on Academy Road. Here at this apartment now, rent is $1050.00. On 2-1-22 the rent will increase to $1,375.00. When all is none I will call on you for help. Thank you. Thank you.
We do not have enough cash or food to last until the end of the month.
I just want to say "Thank You". I greatly appreciate the box of food. It is greatly appreciated.
